items.text: Good and yummy ribs and desserts. And they have very good looking people around. Period.
Great quick taqueria on duxton hill, get there early, great salsa and great drinks - good tequila selection. Oh an pork belly tacos...
Taco so yummy!!!!
Angriest $12 taco i've ever eaten. Actually, ONLY $12 taco I've ever eaten.  I should get into the taco business
Quesadillas are quite delicious! Perfect to sit on the patio and enjoy some cocktails.
Arrogant staff and bad service.
Beef brisket Taco 👍 Grilled corn is nice too.
Lovely location and good food that's gluten-free!
Try the cactus salad. No thorns promise.
Fish tacos por favor
Cool place to hang out but food served is tasty but small portions. Would recommend: Crab Tostaditos 👍 and Chicken Quesadillas 👍
Pork belly taco and snapper taco
Corn is good here
Nice outdoor setting. Look out for crazy Lucha with his portable tequila bar
If you're not a spicy fan, alert them! They make EVERything strong here but the margaritas! #moretequilaplease
Fish taco's!
Slightly pricey for the portions but the food and alcohol is good! Ambience is fun. There's a tall hot muscular Mexican/malay staff there, look out for him!
Corn corn corn,  I am biased here but I only come for the corn.
Very quick service, we enjoyed the pork belly, Lamb and fish tacos. Also sweet corn and beef appetiser. All very tasty with a bit of a kick.
Generally good food and drinks. Great ambience too. Love the grilled corn on the cob and the blue corn cake dessert.
Awesome food! The mojitos are sensational...
The food taste awesome but Way over priced. I liked the salsa selection at Piedra Negra.
Sit at the bar for action. The bar men are skilled and cocktails smooth.
Always busy with a great vibe, must eats include spicy corn on a cob, tostidos, ceviche and tacos! Yum!! Oh and margaritas are pretty tasty too :)
Decent Mexican, but service absolutely ruins it. Good salsa, avoid the guacamole. Also horribly priced drinks menu. Nice to sit outside though.
Lovely ambience, esp the al fresco dining. They don't take reservations for small groups so come early!
One taco is not enought to be consider a meal. Go for a quesadilla instead.
Expensive for the food one is getting.  Have to get 2 tacos and 2 appetisers for a single person to start to feel full. Drinks are very nice though had the virgin margarita. Not sure about returning
Well concocted spices on the corn cob. Fish for sharing is lovely. Great place for a Friday night hangout. If only there was better weather for al fresco dining!
Spicy food!
Frequently crowded. I like the mango ceviche a lot.
Great place for tapas and tequila-based cocktails
Good for after work drinks and pre-party vibe. Bring visitors here. Food is mediocre and overpriced but they have decent tequila!
great food here.read more: http://www.dairycream.blogspot.sg/2013/04/lucha-loco.html
It's been 24 hours and I am already longing for the tofu tacos. Real spicy kick right there. Gimme one nauuuuu
The restroom faucet is a tricky beast. Don't try to unscrew the spout. The trigger is on the floor.
Corn is amazing (spicy)
Overpriced boring food but really nice outdoor setting
A+ for awesome crews! Love the mojitos 😍
Baja Fish is definitely good!
Seeing as it's at Robertson Quay it's actually very good. An engaged chef, interesting menu, consistently good food. A bit populist for me but I find myself returning often.
they only take bookings for large groups, but also hold tables arbitrarily BUT they don't take reservations. They're either rude or incompetent, I can't quite work out which.
Best mexican in Singapore! Avoid the shots from the cart though, they are $25 each and they don't tell you before they pour them. Food is fantastic!
Maybe one of the best Mexicans in Singapore. Try any of the tacos, specially the beef one. Que rico!
So far I have enjoyed most of the dishes I've tried here, but my favourites have gotta be the ceviche de mango, crab tostaditas, and salted caramel & sweet corn ice cream! Flavours pack a punch!
The fish tacos here are good and spicy. Also the 2 choices of ceviche is yummy.
Lamb tacos. Totally legit.
The Elotes are amazing
A beautiful place, but very average and overpriced food / drinks
Not the best Mexican but the tacos are good (especially liked the snapper & pork belly). I'd also recommend the crab tostidas. Quesadillas are nothing to rave about & drinks are pretty standard.
Cosy place, usually crowded. Tacos are real delicious and margaritas definitely worth a try!
A little overrated considering the portions were extremely small and overpriced.They had really good cocktails though.
Elotes. The blue cake. Mojito. That is all.
Not a very expansive food menu, but the tacos are fantastic.
It's all good, but small portions
Nice place for pre- or after-dinner drinks. Unfortunately service is terrible and super slow.
Amazing patron margaritas.
Simple but tasty Mexican food. Can be a little bit too hot. But that's why I like it :)
love the ambience, food, drinks. corn on the cob! chorizo tacos! chicken quesadilla! mojito is refreshing and sangria is not bad. perfect for a chat over a meal!
This place has a cool vibe & great people watching. The food is ok, very authentic. The drink menu is awesome. Really good selection to choose from. The staff is friendly but service needs improving.
Tequila 👆
Love this place. Really good music on weekends. Great drinks and snacks but definitely on the pricier side. Come here with someone who knows the owner :)
Fabulous terrace!
Part of The Loco Group. It also manages Super Loco @ Robertson Quay. Source: Sunday Times
I love the atmosphere but rude waiters will try to steal your plate with still food on it. Feeling of pushing you out asap
The food is good but expensive... $8 for barbecued corn!!!!
Fun atmosphere, strong cocktails and yummy food. Try the passion fruit vanilla cocktail and ceviche
The food is really great, as are the drinks and the atmosphere. Very disappointed with the how the staff handled an error on my bill though, which for me is enough to discourage any return visits.
Get the guacamole, street corn, the snapper fish taco and wash it down with a lot of margaritas!
The guacamole is good.  Mango snapper ceviche was delicious!
Corn on cob! Tender juicy inside.
Tried 3 diff tacos and fav is Baja fish. The corn on cob is expensive at $8 but it is so well done! Order the corn chip with salsa/guacamole to start with. Valet parking available at $7
The food is authentic and delicious tried most of it and its all just yum
Seafood ceviche is scrumptious and so are the softshell tacos. Great outdoor ambiance with the constant breeze, soft piazza lights, music and of cos awesome food.
Gorgeous food!
